<subSubSection id="7CB0CFACFF96FFDB6EF7FD1FFCED52D0" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="34159C27FF96FFDA6EF7FD1FFBB850D7" blockId="4.[151,1127,765,1588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis id="06DE4035FF96FFDA6EF7FD1FFEDB5037" bold="true" box="[151,260,765,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="503BE1D6FF96FFDA6F68FD1FFE795037" author="BONDAR G." box="[264,422,765,788]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" pagination="37 - 38" refId="ref19790" refString="BONDAR G. 1940: A posicao do genero Himatidium na familla dos Crisomelideos e descricao de uma especie nova. O Campo 11: 37 - 38." type="journal article" year="1940">BONDAR (1940)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="F3AAE7A4FF96FFDA6C72FD1FFD495037" authorityName="Bondar" authorityYear="1940" box="[530,662,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Himatidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandoi">
<emphasis id="06DE4035FF96FFDA6C72FD1FFD495037" box="[530,662,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">H. fernandoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a long series of specimens collected in Jequié and Nazareth in Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion id="F66E52C5FF96FFDA6C01FCFFFD7C5017" box="[609,675,797,820]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Bahia</collectingRegion>
. He collected the material on inflorescence of 
<taxonomicName id="F3AAE7A4FF96FFDA6ED3FCDFFD9B5077" authority="(Nees &amp; Mart.) Lindl." authorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityName="Nees &amp; Mart." box="[179,580,829,852]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Calathea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovata">
<emphasis id="06DE4035FF96FFDA6ED3FCDFFE895077" box="[179,342,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Calathea ovata</emphasis>
(Nees &amp; Mart.) Lindl.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F3AAE7A4FF96FFDA6C15FCDFFC6B5077" authority="Linden ex Regel." authorityName="Regel." box="[629,948,829,852]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Calathea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="virginalis">
<emphasis id="06DE4035FF96FFDA6C15FCDFFD275077" box="[629,760,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">C. virginalis</emphasis>
Linden ex Regel.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="F3AAE7A4FF96FFDA6DA0FCDFFB835077" box="[960,1116,829,852]" class="Liliopsida" family="Maranthaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Maranthaceae</taxonomicName>
). Bondar did not specify the exact number of specimens but explicitly stated that the type is in his collection and cotypes in BMNH and MNRJ. I did not have the opportunity to study the collection of Bondar to see how he labelled the type. But since he explicitly mentioned type and cotypes I consider for now the specimens in MNRJ as 
<typeStatus id="EB112285FF96FFDA6C9CFC5FFCB950F7" box="[764,870,957,980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">paratypes</typeStatus>
. It is also unclear, which of the two municipalities is the actual type locality, therefore I cite both in the original spelling.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34159C27FF96FFDB6ED5FC1FFC765230" blockId="4.[151,1127,765,1588]" lastBlockId="5.[113,1090,220,531]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
